The [[Audio Interface]] uses this same clock.

---

## Precision

Each pixel period transmits 28 bits (7 bits × 4 cycles), of which 21 bits are used for RGB data. The remaining capacity is used for control signaling during blanking. No documented mode uses more than 7 bits per channel.

